## Frequently Asked Questions

### How can I confirm a therapist is licensed in Houston?

To confirm a therapist's license in Houston, visit the Texas State Board of Examiners of Professional Counselors website. You can verify credentials and ensure they meet all state requirements. Explore Riaz Counseling for expert support tailored to your mental health needs.

### Do therapists in Houston offer teletherapy or online counseling?

Yes. The compiled information shows that Houston providers offer virtual care and online therapy across Texas. Some directories also list multilingual therapists, which can help you find a safe space where communication feels easier and coping skills are explained in a way that works for you.

### Are there affordable therapy options for people without insurance in Houston?

Affordable options depend on the provider, so ask directly about the cost of therapy, consultations, and any sliding scale availability. Even when a practice is private-pay, a free consultation can help you judge whether the service fits your budget, daily functioning needs, and mental health care goals.\
